    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-28T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/920: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MCK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moser</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-28T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName>: One million dollars deposited
                    today for transfer to branch of National City Bank at Vladivostok to your credit
                    as follows, “Inter-Allied Committer for Supervising Siberian Railways, <persName
                        corresp="#p_SJF1">John F. Stevens</persName>, President Technical Board”.
                    Three million dollars deposited to your credit in same way with Riggs National
                    Bank in this city, as balance of American quota of $20,000,000 for purchase of
                    supplies in this country and maintenance of American personnel connected with
                    operation of railway plan. Inform <persName corresp="#p_SCH1">Smith</persName>
                    at once. Department will cable further details as to drawing on funds in this
                    country. Unless you have serious objections Department would prefer that all
                    your orders be placed through Director General of Military Railways and
                    transmitted through Department. Director General of Military Railways as result
                    of war procedure is equipped with adequate personnel and in close touch with all
                    manufacturers and can act promptly. Hope to answer your June 22, 4 P.M.<note
                        n="76" xml:id="d290fn76">Not printed.</note> concerning your own salary
                    satisfactorily in a few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
